The Lagos Police Rapid Response Squad (RRS) have arrested two robbers and recovered a motorcycle. The suspects are Ayo Taiwo (25) and Jude Prince Ovat (21). Their accomplice, Chibuike Daniel, is at large. A statement on Tuesday by Police spokesman, Benjamin Hundeyin said they were nabbed Sunday night Ovat and Daniel had stopped a rider and asked him to take them from Obalande to Parkview Estate, Ikoyi, where Taiwo was waiting. On arrival, Daniel hit the victim on the head with a wheel spanner and dispossessed him of his motorcycle. Passersby raised the alarm which drew the attention of RRS officers on a routine patrol of the area. The suspects confessed to have stolen several motorcycles in a similar manner and disclosed they sold each for N150,000. Commissioner of Police, Abiodun Alabi has directed RRS Commander, Olayinka Egbeyemi to transfer them to the CPâ€™s Special Squad for further investigation. The statement added that operatives are on the trail of the fleeing gang member, Daniel.